  "label": "Vespera Tertius Thunderwaste Peak",
  "description": "Vespera Tertius Thunderwaste Peak is a solitary basalt mountain rising from ash-choked basins, its flanks cut into vitrified ribs by recurrent electrostatic storms. The summit ridge bears sheets of black rift-glass fused from impact heat, fractured into knife-edged plates that ring faintly under wind and static discharge. Violet lightning routinely crawls along exposed strata, leaving scorched runnels that channel ash into permanent leeward drifts. The bruise-colored auroral glow of the empyrean-stained sky stains the upper slopes, rendering the peak a fixed landmark against the planet’s null-lit horizons.",
